
Overview of adj fragile

The adj fragile has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (3) delicate, fragile, frail -- (easily broken or damaged or destroyed; "a kite too delicate to fly safely"; "fragile porcelain plates"; "fragile old bones"; "a frail craft")
2. (2) fragile -- (vulnerably delicate; "she has the fragile beauty of youth")
3. flimsy, fragile, slight, tenuous, thin -- (lacking substance or significance; "slight evidence"; "a tenuous argument"; "a thin plot"; a fragile claim to fame")
